heaviest_rainfall.status: 21.81mm of rain was recorded as having fallen today, marking an exceptional precipitation event and it ranked 7th out of our records.  A rate of 8.3mm per hour was recorded during the 26.4 hour long storm.  The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 09 November 2025, with precipitation totalling 47.89mm.  The rain fell at 24.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 34.3mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 26.4 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 9th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 21.81mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  On 09 November 2025, the rain lasted for 144.8 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  47.89mm accumulated and it fell at 24.6mm per hour at times.
